    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (77.10) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.92), who both benefit from favorable matchups against pitchers with elevated xERAs. **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, as he faces a soft matchup against Roupp and benefits from wind-out conditions, providing the ideal blend of power and stolen base upside. Similarly, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) is a standout target today; he exploits a massive 6.36 xERA from his opposing starter, with the optimization algorithm rewarding his spot in the #2 hole and a favorable platoon advantage. **Jackson Merrill** (70.77) also presents significant value, buoyed by a 14% park factor boost and a prime hitting environment against a pitcher who struggles to neutralize his platoon split.\n\nRegarding our bench decisions, **Marcell Ozuna** (59.22) was the clear \"first man out,\" missing the cut by less than a point of efficiency. While his power metrics remain stable, he was passed over in favor of higher-upside profiles like **Nasim Nunez** (68.23) and **Andy Pages** (62.83), whose roles as primary runners and situational hitters carry more weight given our aggressive pursuit of the stolen base category. We are monitoring a 42% rain risk in the **Andy Pages** and **Kyle Tucker** game; should that tilt into a delay, we are prepared to pivot to the bench. Furthermore, while **Gunnar Henderson** (57.76) and **Nolan Schanuel** (60.71) are locked into the lineup pending final confirmation, the volatility of the \"Lineup Pending\" status requires us to keep a close watch on **Coby Mayo** and **Josh Jung**, both of whom are ready to sub in should our projected starters lose their order-of-batting advantages.",
